# Browser Screenshot Path

When taking screenshots with `/agent-browser` (`npx agent-browser screenshot`), always specify the output path inside `/Users/esoh/Documents/Labs/VPK-rovodev/output/`. Choose a descriptive filename and subfolder structure that fits the context.

**Never** omit the filename — the default may save screenshots into the current working directory, scattering files across the workspace root.

Examples:

```bash
npx agent-browser screenshot /Users/esoh/Documents/Labs/VPK-rovodev/output/plan-light.png
npx agent-browser screenshot /Users/esoh/Documents/Labs/VPK-rovodev/output/dark-mode-check.png
npx agent-browser screenshot /Users/esoh/Documents/Labs/VPK-rovodev/output/screenshot-2026-02-19T12-00-00.png
```
